u-Kama Doctrine Backup, Pre Pseudocode Edition
Document metadata
System name: u-Kama (legacy reference: BioDollar)
Primary purpose: Coordinate human economic activity under ecological constraint.
Core design separation:
1.
BDR is non financial ecological reserve and ecological memory.
2. BIO is the utility and circulation token used to coordinate, access, validate, and
settle obligation.
Witnessing doctrine: Trias Testium, three independent non sovereign witness
classes.
Core gating doctrine: Ecological Boolean Gate.
Seasonality doctrine: Seasonal endpoints are declared by a Boolean Seasonal
Gate.
Stress doctrine: The seasons are tests, not invoices.
Part I. Canonical axioms and non negotiables
I.1 Inversion axiom
u-Kama places ecology at the centre of monetary design. Economic systems serve
ecological continuity, not the reverse.
I.2 Priceless substrate axiom
We do not price nature, because nature is priceless.
I.3 Constraint without linkage clause
BDR functions exclusively as non financial ecological reserve and record of
witnessed ecological continuity. It does not back, collateralise, peg, reference price,
or ratio link to BIO in any redeemable form.
BIO issuance is never derived from BDR units, balances, or valuations. No peg,
exchange rate, reserve coverage, or redeemability relationship shall exist between
BDR and BIO.
Instead, ecological continuity progressively constrains the conditions under which
BIO may be issued. As ecosystems mature, qualification burden increases through
stricter proof, longer windows, higher verification intensity, higher obligation, and
lower issuance velocity.
BDR remains indifferent to financial activity. BIO absorbs economic stress.
Separation is absolute.
I.4 Doctrine constrains finance
No financial flow or incentive may override the constraints established to protect
ecological continuity. Where ambiguity exists, doctrine prevails over optimisation.
I.5 Failure modes defined in advance
Under stress, u-Kama contracts rather than dilutes. Emergency exceptions are not
permitted.
I.6 Time and truth axiom
Time is the executioner. BDR is the charge sheet.
BDR does not make time legible. It makes claims about endurance falsifiable in time.
Time is meant to be survived, not understood.
I.7 Core operating slogan
u-Kama monetises the interface between external demand and ecological continuity,
not the ecology itself.
BIO may be monetised only at the membrane.
Part II. Core definitions, types, and invariants
II.1 System objects (type catalogue)
EcologicalCell: smallest protocol unit of place bound ecological accounting.
BGU (Base Granular Unit): a witnessed interval of ecological time that remained
intact under declared stress and restraint conditions.
EVU (Ecological Verification Unit): protocol record that attests successful witnessing
of BGUs within defined parameters. EVUs have no independent value or
transferability.
BDR: non financial ecological reserve record, advances only by consecutive validated
BGUs meeting activation thresholds.
BIO: utility and circulation token, exists so obligation can be settled without asking
ecological truth to perform economic work.
AlignmentBond: negative yield or non optimised obligation binding mechanism, not
an investment, confers no entitlement.
AccessBond: bond posted ex ante for extraction or disturbance, to fund rehabilitation
and withdrawal, suspends ecological time accounting for that cell.
ObligationPool: money that exists so failure can be paid for honestly.
PoP Support Pool: operational pool funded by BIO fees, used only to sustain
continuous protection and custodial capacity, non reserve.
II.2 Canonical invariants (must always hold)
1.
BDR is never priced, traded, redeemed, or used as collateral.
2. BIO absorbs all market stress. BDR does not respond to capital, liquidity
pressure, or market signals.
3. Witness classes are independent and non sovereign.
4. Ecological gate resolution is Boolean at protocol layer. Nuance lives above the
state machine.
5. Cells do not offset each other. Failure in one cell does not rewrite another.
6. Seasonal endpoints are declared only by the Boolean Seasonal Gate
(observational witness).
7. Contradiction never selects truth, never rewrites history, resolves as increased
constraint or halted continuity.
8. Success raises the cost of continuation, not the risk of disclosure.
9. Legitimacy arises from named human roles remaining bound to outcomes
through time.
II.3 Minimum cell size
Soft guideline: minimum ecological cell size is 2.083 hectares (about 20,830 square
metres). Cell size is area gauged, not shape defined.
II.4 Pressure Class
Pressure Class is a declared tier that increases obligation and witnessing intensity
without softening outcome thresholds. PoP and PoR gates remain Boolean and
identical across classes, only verification burden and audit frequency scale.
II.5 Subsistence legitimacy clause
Subsistence use is legitimate only within declared bounds under recognised local
authority. Extraction within bounds does not break Protection. Exceeding bounds,
breaching methods, operating outside authority, or converting to market leakage
collapses Protection for the season.
Part III. Roles and authority boundaries
III.1 Role set (protocol roles)
CustodialAuthority: locally legitimate authority that recognises Right of Use and
bounds of use.
Steward: named accountable actor executing protection, management, and on
ground obligations.
Witness (Human): named ranger, transect leader, or designated observer
participating in Human witness class.
ObservationalWitness: non human sensors, aerial or orbital, fixed cameras,
meteorological series.
LaboratoryWitness: soil assays, eDNA, biomass, hydrology samples, biophysical lab
evidence.
VirtualObserver: participant in remote witnessing experience, has no sovereignty.
Subscriber: sits outside custodian, steward, witness participation stack. Cultural
mapping: guest, vaenzi.
GovernanceActor: resolves procedural questions, never ecological truth.
AI: not a witness. AI performs coherence and contradiction analysis only.
III.2 Right of Use (ROU)
Right of Use is the recognised authority to steward an ecological or cultural asset
without owning it, establishing who may act, who is accountable, and who may
legitimately generate Proof within the u-Kama system.
III.3 Sacred Access Doctrine
Sacred knowledge, places, or practices may enter the system only by explicit
permission of recognised elders or custodians. Access remains rare, selective, trust
qualified. Financial contribution never confers entitlement. Silence is protected.
III.4 Exposure Symmetry
A structural condition of participation requiring that any actor benefiting from
ecological continuity remains exposed to the consequences of its interruption.
Exposure symmetry prohibits upside without downside and prevents transfer of
ecological risk to nature.
Part IV. Witnessing doctrine and contradiction
IV.1 Trias Testium
Ecological truth may be recognised only when preserved by three independent, non
sovereign witness classes:
1.
Observational witness class remembers.
2. Human witness class interprets.
3. Laboratory witness class contests and corroborates via independent assays.
AI is not a witness. AI performs contradiction and coherence checks only.
IV.2 Contradiction definition and resolution
Contradiction is incompatible Boolean resolution of the same declared ecological
gate across independent witnesses.
Contradiction never selects truth, never rewrites history, resolves as increased
constraint or halted continuity, leaving time and persistence as the only admissible
arbiters.
IV.3 Default under uncertainty
Uncertainty never relaxes constraint. Absence of adequate witnessing defaults to
failure unless explicit doctrine permits a pause without transition.
Part V. Seasonal Endpoint Doctrine
V.1 Boolean Seasonal Gate
Seasonal endpoints are not calendar based. The Seasonal Gate recognises regime
change through persistent meteorological state under declared thresholds and
persistence rules, with adequate data.
V.2 Witness binding
Within Trias Testium, seasonal state is declared by the Observational Witness
through the Boolean Seasonal Gate. Laboratory and Human witnesses may
corroborate or contradict but may not declare or override. Where contradiction or
ambiguity exists, u-Kama defers settlement and allows time to judge.
V.3 Issuance timing rule
BIO issuance occurs only at ecologically meaningful seasonal endpoints, where
comparable system states can be observed under equivalent stress and recovery
conditions.
Part VI. Ecological Boolean Gate and process clauses
VI.1 Ecological Boolean Gate
At protocol layer, each ecosystem process resolves to Boolean: pass or fail.
Protection requires all declared processes avoid entropy acceleration across
declared stress windows. Regeneration requires directional improvement under
uninterrupted protection.
VI.2 Four process framing
Processes resolve to NOT FAIL for protection:
1.
Water effective or not.
2. Nutrients leaking or not.
3. Community improving or not.
4. Energy capture effective or not.
Protection is the condition under which ecological entropy does not accelerate across
defined stress windows.
Regeneration is directional improvement in energy capture and community dynamics
under uninterrupted protection.
Time is not a process. It is the medium exposing whether protection and regeneration
hold under stress.
Part VII. Protection, Regeneration, Rehabilitation
VII.1 PoP
Proof of Protection functions as a negative constraint on BGU continuity. It does not
generate credit, reward activity, or accumulate value. It determines whether a
witnessed interval remains intact or collapses under stress.
VII.2 PoR
Proof of Regeneration recognises only net ecological state improvement that persists
across defined stress intervals. Effort, expenditure, intent, and compliance have no
independent standing.
VII.3 PoRH and withdrawal binding
PoRH records protection achieved through deliberate human application. PoP
records protection expressed by ecosystems under withdrawal and stress.
Rehabilitation vs regeneration doctrine:
Exogenous engineering may be permitted only if it facilitates re expression of native
ecological processes and can be fully withdrawn without loss of continuity. Any
intervention that must persist indefinitely to prevent collapse is not regenerative.
Withdrawal Test:
Qualification for PoP, and advancement toward PoR, requires post withdrawal
endurance under stress.
VII.4 Drought mortality as information
u-Kama treats drought mortality as information, not indictment.
A drought ceases to be classified as purely natural when acting upon a population
that is artificially immobile, artificially inflated, or artificially concentrated through
human design. In such cases, the system reverts to PoRH and requalification logic
under Withdrawal Test.
Part VIII. BGU, EVU, BDR advancement logic
VIII.1 BGU
A BGU is a witnessed interval of ecological time that remained intact under defined
stress and restraint conditions. BGUs accumulate only through uninterrupted
continuity and have no meaning, value, or transferability outside qualification.
VIII.2 EVU and confidence tiers
EVU is the protocol level verification record attesting that BGUs were successfully
witnessed within declared parameters. EVU confidence tiers are ordinal
classifications ranking robustness based on corroboration, stress exposure, and
reversibility risk, without numeric scoring or financial meaning.
VIII.3 BDR
BDR is recorded accumulation of validated ecological continuity and regeneration
over time, functioning as non financial ecological reserve and ecological memory.
BDR does not promise delivery. It records ecological truth that has persisted under
stress.
BDR advances only upon consecutive validated BGUs meeting activation thresholds.
BDR issuance follows an ecological stock to flow dynamic governed by biophysical
maturity rather than time. No hard cap per site. Scarcity emerges endogenously as
ecosystems mature through Ecological Difficulty Adjustment (EDA), tightening
issuance asymptotically toward zero.
Part IX. BIO and obligation doctrine
IX.1 BIO purpose
BIO exists so that obligation can be settled without asking ecological truth to perform
economic work.
Actors within u-Kama must be able to incur obligation as a condition of participation.
Participation without obligation is impossible.
IX.2 Obligation Pool
Obligation Pool is money that exists so failure can be paid for honestly.
IX.3 EDA
EDA is a rule that makes truth harder to claim the longer it survives.
IX.4 BIO issuance rationale
BIO issuance is front weighted because the greatest contribution is withdrawing
intervention and bearing the risk of being wrong. Highest issuance belongs at the
moment of maximum risk and exposure, not at maturity.
IX.5 Privacy and zero knowledge
Zero knowledge techniques are used so obligation can be settled without becoming a
signal.
BIO to cell linkage may be obfuscated so observers do not infer centralised per
project issuance patterns from transaction flows.
Part X. Bonds, participation, and entitlement boundaries
X.1 Alignment Bonds
Alignment Bonds are non investment participation mechanisms that bind BIO into
negative yield or non optimised obligation under constraint.
They are acquired at market price but confer no yield, governance rights,
acceleration, priority, or entitlement.
Redemption is permitted but unattractive, slow, non strategic, and resets eligibility
pathways.
Alignment Bonds must function identically even if BIO price collapses to zero.
X.2 Access Bonds and extraction doctrine
Extractive activity is permitted within u-Kama provided an Access Bond is posted ex
ante to cover rehabilitation and withdrawal.
Extraction suspends ecological time accounting for the affected cell.
No Protection or Regeneration claims may accrue during disturbance.
Only post withdrawal endurance under stress may re qualify the land for PoP.
Money settles obligation. Time settles truth.
Extraction does not affect continuity, PoP, or PoR status of adjacent cells.
The affected cell is out of service until PoP thresholds are regained.
Part XI. Treasury doctrine and pools
XI.1 Treasury separation
Treasury architecture separates:
1.
Ecological reserve layer, BDR, non financial.
2. Operational cashflow layer, including PoP Support Pool.
3. BIO participation layer, which absorbs volatility and liquidity stress.
XI.2 PoP Support Pool
A defined portion of BIO fees is allocated to the Proof of Protection Support Pool held
within the project treasury.
Funds are strictly operational, used solely to sustain continuous protection,
monitoring, and custodial capacity.
It is financial and spendable, explicitly non reserve, does not reference or back BDR,
and has no influence on issuance thresholds or EDA.
Directionality is one way: BIO fees to PoP Support Pool to protection capacity.
No reverse influence is permitted.
Part XII. CATOS, community as the operating system
XII.1 CATOS axiom
Community is the operating system. Technology, ledgers, and digital systems are
back office support to custodianship, not primary authorities.
Modern conservation succeeds only when it learns to speak in the grammar of
indigenous belief rather than the vocabulary of external control.
XII.2 Anti demoralisation architecture
Anti demoralisation architecture reduces the marginal cost of engagement below the
opportunity cost of withdrawal, without inflating expected returns.
XII.3 Mosaic landscape doctrine
u-Kama projects need not be contiguous. They may be a mosaic of independent
ecological cells within a broader landscape, including explicitly declared community
agriculture cells alongside protection, buffer, and corridor cells.
Agricultural cells are legitimate ex ante declared land uses under local authority. They
are essential to CATOS and subsistence legitimacy.
XII.4 CATOS technology toolbox
Community solutions may be included when compatible with withdrawal and
continuity doctrines. Example held: off grid atmospheric water harvesting paired with
solar, subject to site specific feasibility and local maintenance capacity.
Part XIII. Witnessing interface doctrine, screensaver and emoji
layer
XIII.1 Observe but do not disturb
Core axiom for Virtual Observer offerings: observe but do not disturb.
XIII.2 Screensaver witnessing baseline
A basic subscription may rotate multiple cameras per hotspot on a schedule. Higher
levels may allow selection of viewing, more hotspots, and drones on approved routes
with declared constraints.
XIII.3 Emoji only chat doctrine
Emoji only chat for screensaver witnessing:
No words, numbers, captions, names, tagging. Fixed curated emoji sets only. Emojis
express feeling and acknowledgement, never sightings, counts, claims, or evidence.
Strict rate limits, slow mode always, no threads, no direct messages, no gamification.
Land and feed remain primary.
Core axiom: emojis may express feeling, they may not express knowledge.
Part XIV. Dependency layers, gates, and cell coupling
XIV.1 Dependency declaration
Cells may declare dependency layers for features whose continuity is externally
coupled.
Dependency failure effects are declared ex ante:
1.
Critical dependency failure collapses PoP for the season.
2. Important dependency failure blocks PoR upgrades.
3. Observational dependency failure is recorded without gating effect.
Part XV. Expansion doctrine and immutability
XV.1 Core Expansion Doctrine
A project may expand only by adding new ecological cells whose polygons are
declared ex ante and remain immutable thereafter.
Existing cell polygons may never be modified.
Expansion does not relax thresholds.
Each added cell must independently satisfy entry requirements and witnessing
conditions.
If funding is limited, the project begins with the number of cells it can sustain and
scales outward only as custodial capacity and verification burden remain fully met.
XV.2 Annexation first issuance
First issuance occurs at the moment of first exposure. Each newly annexed cell is a
new exposure surface and qualifies independently for first issuance, subject to
AnnexationAdmissible.
Part XVI. Rectification, exposure protocol, and system integrity
XVI.1 Exposure protocol
Exposure is a prerequisite for state transition.
Exposure to reality functions as governance by ensuring actors remain bound to
outcomes through time. Rectification initiates when witnessing or operational
evidence triggers incompatibility, failure, or breach conditions.
XVI.2 Rectification principle
Rectification never rewrites past recorded truth. It may only pause, constrain, restart,
or require requalification with increased burden.
Part XVII. Reincarnation doctrine, versioning, and fail forward
XVII.1 Reincarnation doctrine
Systems fail not as errors but as exposures. Individual implementations may
terminate without explanation.
Terminations are recorded as reincarnations in versioning history.
Each reincarnation inherits all prior constraints plus any failure induced obligations.
No reincarnation may relax constraints or reinterpret failure.
Continuity belongs to doctrine and ecological truth, not implementations.
XVII.2 Fail forward wording
u-Kama is designed to fail forward. Each failure is retained as structural memory,
tightening future constraint and reducing discretion, so truth accumulates even when
implementations do not endure.
